Job Title: Solution Designer - SAS Experience / Credit Risk
Ad Text:
About the Role

We are seeking an experienced Senior Data Solution Architect (SAS Experience) to lead the design and implementation of enterprise-scale data products within a complex Credit Risk and Banking environment.

This role will be responsible for delivering cross-functional data solutions across multiple platforms, ensuring enterprise reusability, strong governance, and alignment to architecture standards. You will work closely with business stakeholders, service owners, and technical teams to drive high-value data outcomes across risk and analytics programs.

Key Responsibilities

Design and implement cross-functional solutions that deliver enterprise data products across diverse technologies and platforms.

Engineer scalable and reusable data products across sourcing, design, data quality, transformation, and placement layers.

Define and oversee common enterprise components to improve delivery consistency and maintainability.

Architect solutions across multi-technology environments including SAS, Hadoop & Big Data ecosystems, Azure, Azure Machine Learning, Teradata, Informatica, and leading BI platforms.

Collaborate with Credit Risk stakeholders, Tech Leads, Service Owners, and Line of Business Leads to prioritise and size requirements and manage delivery backlogs.

Ensure alignment of projects and programs with enterprise design principles, standards, and governance frameworks.

Partner with business units to define and manage credit risk data elements, including reference data, metadata, and lineage.

Guide Agile delivery teams through design, development, testing, implementation, and support using modern full-stack and DevOps practices.

Skills & Experience

3+ years’ experience within a large, complex Credit Risk and/or Banking environment.

10+ years’ experience delivering business and technology solutions involving complex data engineering processes.

5+ years’ advanced SQL and SAS experience, including Base SAS, SAS Macro, SAS DI Studio, SAS Enterprise Guide, SAS Management Console, and overall SAS platform capability.

5+ years’ experience with Big Data and distributed technologies including Hadoop, Spark, Hive, HBase, Python, Java, Spring Boot, Git, Flink, CosmosDB, Akka, Scala, SQL, and Synapse.

Extensive experience in data warehousing, data modelling, and integration tools such as Informatica and Sterling.

Strong familiarity with BI tools including IBM Cognos/TM1, Power BI, and Tableau.

Proven experience designing cloud-based and serverless architectures, preferably within Microsoft Azure.

Experience delivering Risk Models and Analytics solutions using SAS RFW, SAS Risk Stratum, SAS Viya, and/or Azure Machine Learning.

Hands-on experience with DevOps pipelines, particularly Azure DevOps and Jenkins.

We're reimagining the way Australians live, work, and play. We own and manage some of the most recognisable and loved retail destinations across Australia.

We’re evolving our portfolio into destinations that offer a broad selection of retail, residential, and office spaces. Through our diverse portfolio, data-led decision-making, and nationwide development pipeline, we do things differently.

We’re looking for a Data Platform Manager who’s passionate about building scalable, secure, and high performing data platforms that power everything from analytics to machine learning and AI. In this role, you’ll lead the architecture, development, and operations of our enterprise data platforms—ensuring they are reliable, observable, trusted, and designed to support the organisation’s strategic ambitions. 

You’ll collaborate with engineers, architects, data scientists, analysts, and business stakeholders to create modern data environments that uplift decision making, embed data and AI governance, and accelerate innovation across Vicinity. 

What you’ll be doing 

Platform Architecture 

Design, develop, and maintain scalable data platform architectures aligned with business needs. 

Ensure data quality and seamless integration across multiple systems and sources. 

Own and enforce data security standards aligned to governance and privacy policies. 

Stay across emerging technologies to drive continuous platform innovation. 

Provide technical leadership and mentorship across the data and engineering teams. 

Translate complex data requirements into practical, high quality technical solutions. 

Platform Operations 

Lead day to day operations to ensure our data platforms are stable, secure, and high performing. 

Implement and govern MLOps practices to enable reliable model deployment, monitoring, and lifecycle management. 

Establish monitoring, observability, and alerting across all data pipelines and platforms. 

Coordinate the Data Engineering team to maintain platform reliability and operational excellence. 

Maintain high quality documentation, standards, and operational best practices. 

Partner closely with platform, security, and governance teams to uphold data privacy and compliance. 

Platform Engineering 

Design and manage ETL/ELT processes that ensure efficient, accurate data movement. 

Oversee development of data warehousing and lakehouse solutions that support ML, AI, and analytics. 

Optimise data workflows for performance, scalability, and resilience. 

Monitor, troubleshoot, and continuously improve ETL processes and data availability. 

Work with business and technical stakeholders to shape technical specifications from data requirements. 

What you’ll bring 

Essential Experience 

Bachelor’s degree in Computer Science, Engineering, Mathematics, or similar. 

10+ years in software development, including 7+ years across Data Analytics, Machine Learning, or AI. 

Expertise in data architecture across SQL and NoSQL ecosystems. 

Strong experience deploying containerised solutions. 

Proven capability delivering production grade data pipelines. 

Leadership experience managing Data Engineers and Platform Operations Engineers. 

Critical Knowledge 

Deep experience with at least one major cloud platform (AWS, GCP, or Azure). 

Proficiency in SQL and NoSQL technologies. 

Skilled in Python and JavaScript. 

Strong understanding of Docker and Kubernetes. 

CI/CD experience (e.g., BuildKite) and Gitbased code management. 

Databricks highly advantageous

Capabilities 

Advanced skills in CI/CD and modern DevOps for data and ML workloads. 

Ability to operationalise and deploy data pipelines, ML models, and AI services in containerised environments. 

Strong observability mindset—ensuring data reliability, model quality, and pipeline performance. 

Ability to build and mature data observability practices. 

Excellent communication and stakeholder engagement skills. 

Strength in designing and delivering data platform solutions that enable ML and AI at scale. 

 Why join us? 

At Vicinity, you’ll be stepping into a role that sits at the intersection of data, digital innovation, and enterprise strategy. You’ll shape the foundations of our AI and analytics capabilities and influence how data drives our future. This is a rare opportunity to lead a modern data platform practice in an environment ready to invest, evolve, and innovate.

Our benefits program focuses on creating an awesome place to work in which our people are rewarded and recognised. This includes:

Flexible working options 

Birthday leave & purchased additional leave

$1,000 worth of VCX securities rewarded for eligible team members

Internal mentoring program

Generous Parental Leave

We live and work by our values of Respect, Integrity, Customer Focus, Collaboration and Excellence.  They are the foundation to everything we do and provide us a north star with which we can shape meaningful places where communities connect.

At Vicinity we embrace and celebrate diversity and are committed to creating an inclusive work environment where we attract, retain and develop our people regardless of gender identity, ethnicity, sexual orientation, disability and age. Applications are encouraged from all sectors of the community and we strongly encourage applications from the Aboriginal and/or Torres Strait Islander community.

Our people and our Employee Advocacy Groups (Gender Balance, Cultural Diversity, Disability & Access and Pride & Allies) actively build community and provide allyship within Vicinity. If you’d like to speak to someone to understand what it’s like firsthand to work here, please reach out to our Talent Acquisition team.

Ad Text:
Senior Business Analyst – Innovation Stream


Employment Type: Full Time (35 hours per week)
Duration: 8 Month Contract
Remuneration: Level 9 $148,012 - $157,056 (depending on experience) + 17% super + leave loading
Location:  UNSW Kensington Campus, with fortnightly day trips to Canberra (schedule may vary).

About UNSW:

UNSW isn’t like other places you’ve worked. Yes, we’re a large organisation with a diverse and talented community; a community doing extraordinary things. Together, we are driven to be thoughtful, practical, and purposeful in all we do. Taking this combined approach is what makes our work matter. It’s the reason we’re one of the top 20 universities in the world and a member of Australia’s prestigious Group of Eight. If you want a career where you can thrive, be challenged and do meaningful work, you’re in the right place.

Why Your Role Matters:

This is an exciting opportunity for an experienced Senior Business Analyst with experience in planning, development and delivery of major improvement initiatives. Reporting to the Enterprise Portfolio Management Office (EPMO), you will be deployed to the Canberra City Program, a strategic initiative that will establish UNSW’s new presence in the nation’s capital. The program covers five key streams: Education, Innovation, Operating Model, Estate and Site Technology, building on UNSW’s defence partnerships to drive growth and innovation.

Within this role, you will work across the Innovation stream, with a focus on enabling innovation and supporting the effective onboarding of partners within the innovation ecosystem. You will play a key role in establishing the processes, frameworks and engagement approaches required to successfully support innovation initiatives and partner integration.

Key Responsibilities:

Build effective relationships with stakeholders across the program and university.
Facilitate workshops to capture innovation enablement pain points and align stakeholders.
Lead the mapping and documentation of the innovation journey and processes
Conduct journey mapping for onboarding of innovation partners and translate insights into practical process improvements.
Identify and analyse opportunities to improve service delivery and the innovation partners experience.
Develop service catalogues to clearly identify ownership across service providers.
Contribute to continuous improvement and standardisation across processes.
Develop process map and procedural documentation to UNSW standards.

Skills and Experience:

Relevant tertiary qualification and demonstrated experience with business requirements analysis and business process analysis using appropriate frameworks.
Certified Practitioner in Business Analysis (IIBA or PMP).
Demonstrated experience in applying Lean Six Sigma skills (certification desirable).
Excellent written and oral communication skills.
Strong analytical and problem-solving skills, with a track record as a lateral thinker.
Proven facilitation skills, including workshops with diverse groups (Academics, technical staff, end users).
Strong time management and organisational skills with the ability to deliver to project timeframes.
Understanding of business processes within a tertiary education environment. (desirable).
Understanding of change management principles.
Proven experience in journey mapping and translating insights into service/process improvements.
Strong capability in creating process maps, procedural and operational documents.
Experience working in the innovation industry or higher education (highly desirable).
Experience working on large, complex transformation programs in a consulting capacity.

For further details on role responsibilities and skills & experience required, refer to the position description found under the position listing on Jobs@UNSW

Benefits and Culture:

People are at the core of everything we do. We recognise it is the contributions of our staff who make UNSW one of the best universities in Australia and the world.

Our benefits include:

Flexible working options.
Career development opportunities.
17% Superannuation contributions and additional leave loading payments.
Additional 3 days of leave over Christmas period.
Discounts and entitlements (retail, education, fitness).

For further details on the benefits, please visit https://www.jobs.unsw.edu.au/lifestyle-benefits

How to Apply: Submit your CV & a succinct 1-2 page cover letter detailing your interest and suitability for the job (as per the skills & experience bullet points in the job description) by 11:55pm, 10th March 2026

Please note: Sponsorship is not available for this role, valid Australian working rights are required on application.



Contact: Amy Denney a.denney@unsw.edu.au - Talent Acquisition Team
Please apply directly through the website, applications sent to the contact above will not be accepted.

Aligned with UNSW’s focus on cultivating a workplace defined by safety, ethical conduct, and strong integrity preferred candidates will be required to participate in a combination of pre-employment checks relevant to the role they have applied for.  

These pre-employment checks may include a combination of some of the following checks:  

National and International Criminal history checks

Working With Children Checks

Verification of relevant qualifications

Medical Checks and Assessments 
Compliance with the necessary combination of these checks is a condition of employment at UNSW.

UNSW is committed to equity diversity and inclusion. Applications from women, people of culturally and linguistically diverse backgrounds, those living with disabilities, members of the LGBTIQ+ community; and people of Aboriginal and Torres Strait Islander descent, are encouraged. UNSW provides workplace adjustments for people with disability, and access to flexible work options for eligible staff.

RACV Head Office | Melbourne CBD location 

Permanent Full time | Hybrid working – 3 days in office 

Competitive Salary | Discounts on selected RACV products 

 

RACV is seeking a Manager, Strategy & Insights to play a pivotal role in shaping data led strategy across the enterprise. This role works with senior staff across the organisation, with people leadership, ideal for a strategic thinker who thrives at the intersection of insight, commercial strategy and execution. 

 

 

About the Opportunity  

Reporting to the Head of Strategy, Insights & Reporting, you’ll lead the development and activation of insight-driven strategies that support RACV’s corporate objectives. You’ll partner closely with senior leaders across portfolios to solve complex business problems, translate analysis into compelling recommendations, and support implementation. You’ll also help build enterprise frameworks (segmentation, value propositions, member economics) and coach junior team members. 

 

Key responsibilities 

Partner with senior stakeholders to drive customer led, commercially viable strategy  

Lead strategic analysis, modelling and insight generation to inform decision-making  

Develop and embed enterprise frameworks, metrics and strategic roadmaps  

Champion a cross portfolio, member-centric perspective  

Build industry and market insight to inform strategic direction  

Coach and develop strategy and insight capability within the department and broader 

 

About you 

Degree in a relevant business discipline (e.g. Commerce, Economics, Marketing)  

8+ years’ experience in data led strategy, insights or consulting within a bluechip or complex environment  

Strong commercial acumen with advanced analytical and storytelling skills  

Proven ability to influence senior leaders and operate in ambiguity  

Experience leading strategic projects end-to-end and developing team capability 

 

 

 

There’s so much on offer when you join RACV with benefits including  

  

Our flexible and informal work environment which helps bring balance between work and home.  

Generous discounts on home and car insurance policies and RACV roadside care  

Club Membership and great discounts across all RACV resorts  

Discounts from corporate partners that are updated monthly.  

  

 

 

Our difference  

  

At RACV, we believe that maintaining a diverse and inclusive workplace is an important element in our continued success. We want our people to feel welcome, supported and appreciated for who they are and what they bring to our business.  

Ready to reach your full potential? Join our team, where the work is more meaningful and making a difference beyond the work matters.  

  

 

Application Process  

  

You can learn more about the RACV at careers.racv.com.au  

Applicants will be required to provide evidence of their eligibility to work in Australia, and consent to a criminal record check.  

Submit your CV via the link below.

About the role:
 
Our client is seeking a commercially astute and highly confident Senior Financial Analyst to join their high-performing finance team based on Sydney's Lower North Shore.
 
As a trusted Finance Business Partner to Sales and Commercial leaders, you will play a pivotal role in driving revenue performance, margin improvement and disciplined cost management across the division. Operating in a fast-paced, performance-driven environment, you will bring sharp financial insight, strong commercial acumen and the confidence to challenge senior stakeholders. 

This organisation values personality, presence and impact. You will thrive here if you are outgoing, proactive, and comfortable influencing decision-makers while building strong cross-functional relationships. 
 
Key Responsibilities:  

Act as a trusted Finance Business Partner to Sales and Divisional Leaders 
Deliver detailed commercial analysis and deep dives to support pricing, promotions and investment decisions 
Lead financial planning, budgeting, forecasting and P&L management with a focus on revenue, margin and cost control 
Translate complex data into clear, actionable insights for senior stakeholders 
Analyse financial and non-financial impacts of commercial initiatives 
Partner closely with Sales, Finance and Operational teams to drive performance outcomes 
Identify cost-saving and efficiency opportunities across the division 
Support continuous improvement initiatives and strengthen financial acumen across the business
What We Are Looking For:      

You are a commercially minded finance professional with a strong background in FMCG or large, brand-led organisations. You understand revenue drivers, pricing levers and customer economics — and you enjoy being embedded within the commercial side of the business. 

You bring: 

CPA or CA qualification
5+ years’ experience in a commercially focused finance role
Proven business partnering experience with the ability to influence at all levels 
Strong pricing and margin analysis capability 
Advanced Excel and analytical skills with experience working across large data sets 
The confidence to challenge assumptions and drive better commercial outcomes 
Most importantly, you are personable, confident and comfortable operating in a high-energy environment. You build trust quickly, communicate clearly and are not afraid to have robust commercial conversations when required. 

How to Apply
To apply online, please click on the appropriate link below. Alternatively, for a confidential discussion, please contact Jack Billingham on jbillingham@sharpandcarter.com.au, quoting Ref #JBL30193

The Company…..
Our client is a NSW Government organisation dedicated to delivering efficient, high-quality services across the state while supporting strong and sustainable community outcomes. Each business unit is led by experienced and committed professionals who collaborate on initiatives designed to improve and streamline government service delivery.

The successful candidate will bring proven experience providing commercial insights and strategic advice to senior stakeholders. This role is based in Parramatta, with flexible hybrid working arrangements available. An immediate start is required for an initial six-month contract, with the potential for extension.    


The Job…..
Reporting to the Finance Manager in this project-based Senior Financial Analyst role, you will be responsible for:

Prepare and submit all PTA and carry-forward requests accurately and on time.
Deliver monthly management reports and PMO financial updates.
Review and reconcile general ledger and cost centre accounts.
Lead accurate budget planning, forecasting, tracking and reporting activities.
Partner with eight Project Managers to provide real-time financial analysis, manage budget performance and support delivery outcomes.
Provide strategic financial advice and assurance to the Program Director.
Deliver detailed financial modelling, costing and analysis to support project briefs and initiation documents, and provide expert advice across teams.
Prepare clear, accurate and timely responses to Ministerial and senior stakeholder requests, including ad hoc financial queries.
 
You…..
To be successful in this role, you must have experience in the following:

Minimum two years’ experience in a Financial Analyst role within a large or complex organisation.
Big 4 consulting experience highly regarded.
SAP experience strongly preferred.
Advanced Excel capability essential.
Strong interpersonal and communication skills, with the ability to engage effectively with stakeholders.
Demonstrated ability to work autonomously, manage competing priorities and deliver to tight deadlines.
  
How to apply…..
Don’t miss this opportunity to work for a company that really looks after its people!  Please apply directly through the relevant job board. 

Please be advised only shortlisted candidates will be contacted.
 
We take the security of our candidates seriously and will never ask for your bank details during the hiring process nor will we contact you via WhatsApp or Telegram. If you receive any communication from us requesting this information, please do not respond and contact us immediately.

Description
The Foxtel Group is transforming how we leverage data, machine learning, and insights to drive smarter decision-making. We hold the richest and most comprehensive datasets in the Australian entertainment industry, capturing the detailed behavioral and viewing habits of over five million subscribers across Sports, Entertainment, and News.


We are currently recruiting a BI Reporting Manager within our Growth and Analytics team, to take full ownership of Foxtel’s reporting environments, standard metrics, and processes. As a strong process leader, you will seamlessly blend technical expertise across SQL, data warehouses, lakehouses, and Tableau with exceptional people leadership and stakeholder engagement skills.


In this pivotal position, you will deliver trusted, high-quality performance reports that empower our leaders to make confident, data-driven decisions. You will champion fit-for-purpose Ways of Working, establishing clear expectations for both your team and stakeholders regarding our service offerings, backlog management, prioritisation, quality assurance, and resource planning.




Key Responsibilities
Produce trusted, high-quality performance reports that empower Foxtel leaders to make confident, data-driven decisions.
Ensure robust governance and processes are in place, maintain clear expectations for stakeholders and your team regarding service offerings, backlog management, prioritisation, and QA.
Oversee data controls, standardisation, change management and overall data management across the entire reporting function. 
Proactively identify opportunities for improvement and continuously drive operational efficiencies in resourcing, workflows, and costs. 
Lead, mentor, and motivate a team of analysts and developers, fostering a highly collaborative environment focused on technical excellence and continuous professional 


About your experience
Demonstrated experience leading, managing, and mentoring data analytics and reporting teams, particularly managing a mix of onshore and offshore resources.
Strong technical skillset in developing, optimising, and testing SQL code, with a deep understanding of relational databases and data warehousing concepts. 
Significant experience working with massive datasets to surface meaningful insights. 
High proficiency in leading visualisation tools such as Tableau, Power BI, or Looker. 
Sharp commercial instincts with a deep understanding of business levers, balancing analytical rigor with what truly drives impact. 
Proven track record in process standardisation, governance, and backlog management. 
Exceptional interpersonal and communication skills, serving as an open collaborator with a proven ability to influence outcomes across all levels of the organisation through clear and concise messaging. 
Previous experience in Contact Centre and/or audience reporting within the media or entertainment sector is advantageous.


Life at Foxtel Group 
A career with us means working across one or more of our brands including Foxtel, Hubbl, Kayo Sports, BINGE, Flash, Fox Sports and Foxtel Media. When you join, the Perks at Work are taken care of:  
You’re part of Fox Flex, our hybrid way of working with time spent at home and on campus  
Free & discounted products including Foxtel, Hubbl, Foxtel Broadband, Kayo Sports and BINGE  
Special days away from work for Birthday, Cultural & Volunteer Leave  
Access to our holistic Fox Fit wellbeing program  
Company-wide meeting-free lunch hours and Friday afternoons

The Opportunity

In a rapidly evolving digital landscape, Elysium Digital partners with federal and state government agencies, as well as private sector organisations, to design and deliver human-centred services that create measurable impact. As a Senior Service Designer, you will lead complex, end-to-end service transformation initiatives, combining deep research capability, systems thinking, and product mindset to shape meaningful, scalable outcomes.
 
You will work across discovery, design and delivery - guiding multidisciplinary teams, influencing senior stakeholders, and embedding evidence-based decision-making into digital and service ecosystems. If you're driven by solving complex problems, improving real-world services, and translating research insights into tangible product and service improvements, this is your opportunity to lead change at scale. You'll join a collaborative, flexible and high-trust culture where professional growth, innovation and impact are highly valued.

Location: Canberra/Sydney/Brisbane (Hybrid – Onsite/Remote)

We can also offer an initial contract until June 30th 2026.
 
What Will You Do?

As a Senior Service Designer at Elysium Digital, you will:

Lead End-to-End Service Design Engagements
Design and deliver complex service transformation initiatives across government and enterprise.
Map current and future state services across people, process, policy and technology.
Identify systemic pain points and opportunities for measurable improvement.
Lead Research & Insight Generation
Plan and conduct qualitative and quantitative research (interviews, usability testing, co-design sessions, field studies, surveys).
Synthesise findings into actionable insights, service blueprints, journey maps and opportunity backlogs.
Embed evidence-based decision-making throughout delivery.
Apply a Product Mindset
Translate service insights into product strategies, MVP definitions and prioritised roadmaps.
Collaborate closely with product managers, designers and engineers to ensure services are scalable, viable and desirable.
Support iterative delivery using agile methodologies.
Facilitate Co-Design & Stakeholder Alignment
Lead workshops and collaborative sessions with executives, policy owners, technical teams and frontline staff.
Align diverse stakeholders around shared service outcomes and measurable impact.
Communicate complex service ecosystems clearly and confidently.
Drive Client Relationships & Growth
Build trusted relationships with senior stakeholders.
Contribute to proposals, RFQs and capability development.
Identify opportunities to extend value across accounts.
Strengthen Practice & Thought Leadership
Refine and evolve Elysium Digital's service design, research and product methodologies.
Contribute to internal capability uplift and mentoring of junior designers.
Stay current with emerging service design, research and digital product trends.
What Makes You a Good Fit?
We're looking for someone who:

Thinks in systems and designs holistically across service ecosystems.
Balances strategy with hands-on delivery.
Has strong research capability and can confidently lead discovery phases.
Understands product thinking - including roadmaps, MVPs, backlog prioritisation and agile delivery.
Translates complexity into clear, actionable service improvements.
Demonstrates emotional intelligence, sound judgement and strong stakeholder management.
Communicates effectively with audiences ranging from delivery teams to executive leadership.
Is adaptable and comfortable working across sectors and regulatory environments.
At Elysium Digital, we foster a friendly, open and collaborative culture built on integrity, professionalism and delivering meaningful outcomes.
 
You'll benefit from:

Hybrid working model: Flexible approach that balances remote work with on-site collaboration at client offices.
High-impact projects: Work that improves essential public and private sector services.
Career progression: A structured consulting pathway supporting leadership and capability growth.
Balance & flexibility: A culture that respects both personal and professional priorities. 
If you're passionate about designing impactful services, leading research-driven transformation, and bringing a strong product mindset to complex environments, we'd love to hear from you.

You MUST be an Australian Citizen and hold a minimum of a Baseline Security Clearance to be considered for this position.

For more information contact Mitchell on 0425 269 780

Only shortlisted candidates will be contacted for these position.

Slater and Gordon Lawyers are a leading personal injury and class actions law firm where every member of our team has a shared passion for our clients: we are people caring for people.

Our commitment to our people includes offering genuine work-life balance, with a hybrid work environment allowing them to split their time between home and the office. We recognise and reward high performance and have outstanding employee benefits including a week of shutdown leave, paid parental leave, extra-long service leave, together with various ongoing learning and professional development opportunities.

About the role

This is a senior, hands-on quality assurance role focused on safeguarding the accuracy, integrity and reliability of business critical data and reporting. Reporting to the Data Lead and sitting within our IT function, you will play a key role in major transformation initiatives as we modernise our legacy legal systems and implement a new cloud-based SaaS platform.
You will lead quality assurance across complex data migrations, ETL pipelines, system integrations and Power BI reporting, ensuring that data is transformed correctly, reconciled thoroughly and surfaced accurately for operational and executive decision making. This role combines deep technical expertise with strong stakeholder engagement and a passion for raising QA standards across data and analytics.

What you'll do?




Define and execute risk-based test strategies for complex data migration, integration and reporting programs
Validate ETL workflows, transformation rules, batch processes and incremental loads across legacy and cloud platforms
Perform detailed reconciliation testing to confirm data completeness, accuracy and consistency
Validate Power BI dashboards, KPIs and semantic models using advanced SQL interrogation of source systems
Oversee data quality checks, automation approaches and API testing practices
Manage defect tracking, test execution reporting and evidence traceability

What will you bring?




You will bring deep experience in data and reporting focused QA, combined with strong analytical capability, curiosity and a passion for quality. You will have hands on experience testing ETL workflows, data migrations, system integrations and enterprise reporting platforms, alongside advanced SQL skills and strong attention to detail. You will be comfortable working in complex hybrid environments and confident engaging with both technical and non-technical stakeholders. Experience with Power BI, API testing and cloud based data platforms is essential, while exposure to Azure data services, automation frameworks and regulated industries such as legal, financial or professional services will be highly regarded

What next?

If you are interested in this opportunity, please apply directly to Slater and Gordon. We prefer to talk with you personally and are not accepting applications from recruitment agencies.

To be eligible for this position, you must be an Australian citizen, a permanent resident, or hold a valid visa with full and unrestricted working rights in Australia. Proof of work rights will be required as part of the Slater and Gordon application process.

Your New Role

We have a 12-month max-term contract opportunity for Senior Change Analyst to join the Enterprise Group Delivery team and support organisational change projects activities. This role provides change planning, analysis, communications, learning support and measurement and monitoring of change metrics. The Senior Change Analyst may also lead small / medium scale change activities and supports change managers in the delivery of larger scale change projects/programs.

This role is instrumental in supporting stakeholders across the Fund by analysing, planning, developing and embedding effective change, communications and training plans to support both adoption and benefits realisation.

Key responsibilities will include;


Support Change Managers in the delivery of the approved change management plan.
Conduct change impact and change readiness analysis and assessments by applying a structured change management methodology.
Draft current, transition and future state for impacted stakeholders.
Work with stakeholders and/or senior change practitioners to identify all impacted stakeholders.
Document stakeholder maps, stakeholder assessments, sponsor roadmaps and other artefacts associated with managing and delivering the change plan.

Own NPV, IRR and scenario analysis for development projects
Support acquisitions and major investment decisions
Attractive hybrid work model | Energy Discounts | Career Growth Opportunities

Alinta Energy is one of Australia’s biggest energy retailers, generators and developers with over 1.1 million customers. Australia’s energy system is undergoing the biggest transformation in its history and we’re right there with it. We’re investing in and developing large-scale renewables and storage projects as part of our ongoing effort to provide our customers with reliable, affordable and sustainable energy.

We understand that flexibility matters when considering your next role. Let us know your requirements, and we’ll carefully consider how we might accommodate them.

Ready to make a real impact?

This is a pivotal role within Alinta Energy’s Power Development team, responsible for shaping investment decisions across a growing portfolio of renewable, storage and gas generation projects. Sitting within the Power Development team, this role leads the commercial and financial evaluation of major capital investments, owning the investment case from early development through to financial investment decision. It is a hands‑on, technically focused leadership role — ideal for a senior investment professional who enjoys being close to the modelling while guiding high‑quality decision‑making and developing analytical capability within a lean, high‑performing team.

Why you’ll love working here

At Alinta Energy, we’re taking real action to deliver reliable and sustainable energy for Australia — and that practical approach runs through everything we do. You’ll get clear direction, genuine flexibility, and the support you need to grow, all while working on projects that make a lasting difference. We’re big enough to create impact, but small enough that your ideas and effort will always be seen.

There are plenty of other great benefits of working for Alinta Energy, including flexible working, energy discounts, an Employee Assistance Program (EAP), a paid volunteer day each year, fully stocked kitchens, and lots more.

What you'll do

Lead end‑to‑end commercial and financial appraisal of development projects, including feasibility assessments, business cases and investment recommendations
Build, review and challenge complex financial models (NPV, IRR, sensitivities, scenario analysis, project finance and debt sculpting), remaining hands‑on with key assumptions and outputs
Apply company assurance standards and lead due diligence processes for new development and acquisition opportunities
Work closely with Treasury to develop and assess project funding strategies, including debt and equity structures, capital structure and financial risk considerations
Lead and develop the Investment Analyst, setting high analytical standards and building strong modelling and commercial capability across the team

Your experience

6–10 years’ experience in investment banking, Big 4 corporate finance/modelling, project finance, or corporate development within an ASX‑listed or infrastructure‑focused organisation
Advanced financial modelling capability, including complex project finance and valuation models, with strong Excel and PowerPoint skills
Experience supporting or leading project financing, credit analysis, debt sizing and capital structure evaluation
Demonstrated leadership capability, with experience coaching, mentoring or managing analysts and a genuine interest in developing others
Strong commercial judgement and stakeholder influence, with the ability to translate complex analysis into clear, well‑reasoned recommendations for senior leaders

Please note this role requires full working rights within Australia.

Like what you’re seeing?

If you like the sound of this, and you’ve got experience in a similar role, we’d love to talk to you. Come and discover better together with Alinta Energy.

We are a 2026 Circle Back Initiative Employer – we commit to respond to every applicant.

If your application progresses, we will need to complete background and pre-employment checks, such as immigration checks, reference checks, criminal background checks, qualification checks, and additional checks for roles related to finance.

Our Diversity Commitment

Alinta Energy offers a truly diverse, safe and supportive work environment. As an equal opportunity employer, Alinta Energy encourages applications from any qualified person, including First Nations Australians, members of the LGBTQIA+ community, people of all ages and people living with a disability. We are also proud to be a WORK180 Endorsed Employer and we are committed to advancing women’s careers.

We look forward to hearing from you.

About Brisbane City Council 

Brisbane City Council is Australia’s largest local government, responsible for shaping one of the fastest growing capital cities in the country. Council’s Brisbane Vision 2031 sets out the city’s long term aspirations: to be safe, inclusive, prosperous and globally connected, while retaining the lifestyle, character and subtropical vibrancy that make Brisbane unique. 

In the lead up to the 2032 Olympic and Paralympic Games, Council is entering a defining era of transformation and reform. This is a once in a generation opportunity to deliver city shaping projects, integrated planning frameworks and sustainable economic development that will leave a lasting legacy. 

About the Role 

Reporting to the Chief Financial Officer, the Manager, Financial Planning and Analysis is a senior executive leadership role within Strategic Finance, positioned at the centre of financial decision-making for one of Australia’s largest and most complex local governments. 

You will lead the transformation of Council’s FP&A capability through modern planning frameworks, rolling forecasts, advanced financial modelling, digital tools and data-driven insights, ensuring finance is future focused, agile and decision relevant. 

This is an opportunity to shape how finance partners with the business. You will act as a visible and trusted advisor to executive and operational leaders, with a clear mandate to challenge assumptions, elevate financial literacy and strengthen decision-making discipline across Council. 

The role offers significant visibility across the organisation and the opportunity to influence outcomes that directly impact the future of Brisbane. As a member of Council’s executive leadership cohort, you will contribute beyond the FP&A function, participating in organisational strategy, governance and reform initiatives and supporting enterprise-wide performance excellence. 

Key aspects of the role include: 

Leading the development of Council’s annual budget, long-term financial plan and forecasting framework, ensuring alignment with strategic priorities and service delivery outcomes 
Providing high-quality financial modelling, scenario analysis and insights to support executive decision-making and major initiatives 
Establishing and embedding a strong finance business partnering approach across diverse service areas 
Driving continuous improvement in financial planning processes, systems and analytics capability 
Translating complex financial information into clear, practical insights that support confident and timely decisions 
Leading and developing a high-performing team while contributing to broader organisational strategy and transformation initiatives 
This role will suit a finance leader who enjoys operating in a complex environment, influencing beyond traditional finance boundaries and building capability across an organisation. It offers the opportunity to combine strategic thinking with tangible impact, supporting long-term financial sustainability and delivering value for the Brisbane community. 

As an Executive Service leader, you will contribute beyond the FP&A function, participating in whole-of-Council strategy, governance, reform and performance initiatives. This includes engaging with senior executives and elected members, and providing trusted, independent financial advice in complex, high-accountability environments. 

About You 

You are an experienced enterprise FP&A leader with strong financial planning and analysis capability and a demonstrated ability to influence decision-making in complex organisations. You bring a strategic mindset, balanced with strong operational understanding, and are comfortable working closely with senior executives to drive outcomes. 

You will demonstrate: 

Extensive experience in financial planning and analysis, budgeting and forecasting within a large or complex organisation 
Advanced financial modelling and scenario planning capability 
A strong track record of business partnering with executive and operational leaders 
The ability to translate complex financial data into clear commercial insights and recommendations 
Experience improving financial systems, processes or planning frameworks 
Strong stakeholder engagement and influencing skills across diverse groups 
A collaborative and people focused leadership style with experience building high performing teams 
A strong understanding of public sector governance, accountability frameworks and the unique challenges of local government finance 
Experience operating in, or closely with, highly regulated or public accountability environments, with a strong understanding of governance, stewardship and legislative context. 
To be eligible for this position, tertiary qualifications in accounting, business or a related discipline are required. You must hold CPA or CA accreditation (or equivalent Australian recognition). Postgraduate qualifications in management or public administration will be highly regarded.
